🎯 Aim
To create an Executive Summary page and implement a Visual Walkthrough in Power BI using multiple report pages, visuals, slicers, and navigation buttons for effective data presentation.
________________________________________
🧩 Algorithm (12 Points)
1.	Open Power BI Desktop.
2.	Click Home → Get Data → Excel and load PowerBI_Executive_Summary_Practice.xlsx.
3.	Rename the first report page as Executive Summary.
4.	Insert Card visuals to display Total Sales and Count of Products.
5.	Insert a Bar Chart with Product on Axis and Sales on Values.
6.	Insert a Pie Chart with Region on Legend and Sales on Values.
7.	Insert a Line Chart with Date on Axis and Sales on Values.
8.	Add a Slicer and drag Category into it for interactivity.
9.	Add a new page and rename it Product Details.
10.	Insert a Table and Bar Chart to show detailed Product and Sales information.
11.	Add another page named Region Analysis and create visuals for Region-wise sales.
12.	Insert Buttons with Page Navigation to move between pages, creating a Visual Walkthrough of the report.

